ash <br>Plate - 10% Penalty vs Crush, 5% Bonus vs Slash, 5% Bonus vs Thrust <br><br>**Note, there are other armor types with bonuses and penalties for mobs. Bony Undead for example have a bonus vs Thrust, but a huge penalty vs Crush. I just displayed player armor types. <br><br>Ok so now we understand that, lets move on to enchanting bonuses. To start I'll use cloth cause there's no base bonus or penalties. <br><br>Lets say Max gets some player made AF40 cloth armor, full set, and enchants it to 25%, which is I believe what nightshade cloth gets if you enchant it. Max's armor will now have a 25% bonus to all weapon types. Thrust, Crush and Slash. <br><br>Leather for example, if I have a 20% bonus on my armor, I'll have a 5% bonus vs slash, and a 35% bonus vs thrust and a 20% bonus vs crush, from the above table. Just add it to your armor's base bonuses. <br><br>This is all base mind you, mobs probably have their own bonuses to go on. Also players can enchant their weapons. Or have bonuses applied on dropped/quest weapons. <br><br>So with that in mind, if I have a 20% bonus on my armor, I have 5% bonus vs slash, 20% vs crush and 35% vs thrust, however, if my opponent has a slashing weapon with 20% bonus, it negates my bonus on my armor. If my armor is 20% bonus, and my Midgard opponent has a 25% bonus sword, my effective bonus for that encounter is in fact a 20% penalty. Follow... <br><br>Base leather vs slash, 15% penalty <br>Add my armor's 20% bonus, now have 5% bonus vs slash <br>Add my opponent's 25% weapon bonus, I now have a 20% penalty this causes me no end of problems vs Midgard Bersekers. <br><br>More! <br>When you get hit, you'll notice that you get hit in a certain spot. Head, torso, arm, etc. So when you get swung at, your total AF is checked, as well as your body part being hit, and that piece of armor is checked for bonuses and such, a hit or miss happens, and damage is applied if hit, based on some extremely odd formula which I cannot fathom at this time. <br><br>Also, each piece of armor has different additions to total AF, example, your jerkin gives you more protection than your gloves =) Again I'm not sure of values here, but this is the order it goes in. Vest, Legs, Sleeves, Hat, Boots/Gloves. Boots and gloves are the same. <br><br>/Rod <br><br>They said, &quot;Impress strongly the Word upon them&quot;, <br>so I carved the scripture upon my quaterstaff and <br>&quot;Impressed the Word&quot; upon them, as hard and as <br>often as I could. <br><br> <p><div align="center"><img src="http://www.nhbzone.com/up4it/up4it_images/maxricco.jpg"</div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uklumzepuller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Klumze Puller</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 3:02:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=197.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Noob Question</span><hr size=1> You the man...thanks <p>Bish Blackburn 41st Level Paladin Lancelot<br>Zergling Enforcer 33rd Theurgist Lancelot<br><br><html><body><center><img src="http://klumze.homestead.com/files/ice2.jpg"></center></body><html> <br>Theurgist Mobster</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umahdi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mahdi</A>&nbsp;